  <thing id="wS2Ribbonw" name="Ribbonweave" description="This weapon appears to be a short cane or walking stick carved with abstract designs that give it a variety of weird protrusions and handholds. In its normal form, the ribbonweave functions as a club, but it features a catch that can be triggered as a free action, releasing a flexible sharp-edged metal ribbon from the end of the stick.\n\nYou can use the Weapon Finesse feat to apply your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls with a ribbonweave sized for you, even though it isn&apos;t a light weapon. You can&apos;t wield a ribbonweave in two hands in order to apply 1-1/2 times your Strength bonus to damage rolls.\n\nRibbonweaves are popular among changelings because they are easily concealed. A DC 18 Search check is required to determine that the ribbonweave is a weapon.\n\n{b}Pathfinder:{/b} This is setup as a racial equipment for the Eberron Changeling race." compset="Weapon">
